name: Australian Aboriginal
description:
Keyboard layout for typing Australian Aboriginal languages. In this keyboard — 
• The '[' key produces: ŋ
• The ']' key after a vowel adds an umlaut to a vowel (e.g. ä).
• The '/' key after a consonant adds an underscore to the consonants d, l, n, r, and t (e.g. ṉ).
• The '`' key before a key gives the standard Latin character for the key, instead of the key above.
